intro: Seseli webbii, commonly known as the Webb's Seseli, is a flowering plant native to the mountainous regions of Central Asia. It belongs to the Apiaceae family, which includes carrots and parsley, and is characterized by its slender stems and compound leaves. The plant produces small, greenish-yellow flowers arranged in umbels, typical of the family. Seseli webbii is often found in rocky or gravelly soils at high elevations. Its botanical features make it an interesting subject for ecological and taxonomic studies.
